snippet.textDisplay:
The real sin about the Marvel Cinematic Universe (MCU), including the Tom Holland (TH) Spider-man Movies, is the MCU is on Earth-199999, not the Marvel Main Continuity of Earth-616. Even though, in this movie, Mysterio states this Peter Parker/Spider-man is on Earth-616 and he's from Earth-833 (shown in the above video at 7:36). That's incorrect. You can google it. So all the changes in this Spider-man Franchise are Canon for that universe. Michelle Jones is MJ, not Mary Jane Watson. The real MJ of Earth-616 and Gwen Stacy most likely won't appear in this movie franchise.


Flash Thompson is a "Nerd Bully". This isn't feasible. A kid like this bullying Peter is unbelievable. Betty Brant and Ned Leeds are Teenage High School Students. Spider-Sense is downplayed as a "Peter Tingle" and in the TH Spider-man Franchise, it doesn't work very well. The way he admits he's Spider-man to MJ in this movie was a joke, but again, it's a different universe. Like Star Trek, The Original Series Writer Dorothy Fontana (known as D.C. Fontana in the series credits) stated, "Canon is what writers need it to be". It's so true for the MCU.


Have we forgotten Uncle Ben's death because of Peter's failure to stop the robber when he had the chance to, substantiates Uncle Ben's saying of "With Great Power there comes Great Responsibility." Isn't that what motivates Peter Parker to be Spider-man? Or is Tony Stark the main motivation, in this universe, for Peter Parker to be Spider-man? Uncle Ben is downplayed in this MCU and Aunt May in this universe doesn't seem shaken by his death at all. Is this TH Spider-man version, the one we know and have followed for almost 6 decades? On Earth-616, that version of Peter Parker/Spider-man would be the natural choice to be Tony Stark's successor, not this TH version of Spider-man on Earth-199999. Wouldn't Tony Stark know from Spider-man Homecoming, that this Peter Parker isn't ready to "hand over" Edith to? "Far from Home" was OK, but it's an alternate universe, not the Marvel Main Continuity.


I can wait for Spider-man 3. In the upcoming movie, logically Dr. Strange will have to use a spell to make people forget Peter Parker is Spider-man or one of the Skrulls or another Super Hero like Daredevil will have to put on the costume and swing by while TH's Peter Parker is standing there. It'll be interesting what the storyline of Spider-man 3 will be. Will Norman Osborn be in the plotline? If so, will Harry Osborn also be there? What Villain or Villains will he fight? Will the Authorities believe this "doctored" video and try and arrest Peter? Will Peter Parker be on the run? I think this is soo much to cover, either Spider-man 3 will be 3 hours long or have the slim possibility of being two parts. I hope the former.


However, no matter how you criticize this movie or not for its "sins", one thing is for sure, it's an alternate universe. "Canon" can be anything the writers want it to be for the next storyline. All I know is, do I want to watch movies, TV shows, animated features, or cartoons about characters from other universes? Probably not. I'm a fan of the "Multiverse", but not when ALL the stories from DC and Marvel are from alternate universes. Making money is the bottom line for all these movies and no matter what the omissions, errors, or unbelievable storylines the writers come up with today's audiences seem fine with anything they put on the big screen just so they're entertained. That's OK, but at some point, there have to be consistencies in the plotlines. Just an opinion and thanks for reading.
